{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:first-timothy.2",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
    "chapterNumber": 2,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Timothy 2 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-timothy.2.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:1",
      "text": "First of all, then, I urge that supplications, prayers, intercessions, and thanksgivings be made for all men,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-timothy.2.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:2",
      "text": "for kings and all who are in high positions, that we may lead a quiet and peaceable life, godly and respectful in every way.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-timothy.2.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:3",
      "text": "This is good, and it is acceptable in the sight of God our Savior,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-timothy.2.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:4",
      "text": "who desires all men to be saved and to come to the knowledge of the truth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-timothy.2.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:5",
      "text": "For there is one God, and there is one mediator between God and men, the man Christ Jesus,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-timothy.2.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:6",
      "text": "who gave himself as a ransom for all, the testimony to which was borne at the proper time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-timothy.2.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:7",
      "text": "For this I was appointed a preacher and apostle (I am telling the truth, I am not lying), a teacher of the Gentiles in faith and truth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-timothy.2.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:8",
      "text": "I desire then that in every place the men should pray, lifting holy hands without anger or quarreling;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-timothy.2.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:9",
      "text": "also that women should adorn themselves modestly and sensibly in seemly apparel, not with braided hair or gold or pearls or costly attire",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-timothy.2.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:10",
      "text": "but by good deeds, as befits women who profess religion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-timothy.2.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:11",
      "text": "Let a woman learn in silence with all submissiveness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-timothy.2.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:12",
      "text": "I permit no woman to teach or to have authority over men; she is to keep silent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-timothy.2.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:13",
      "text": "For Adam was formed first, then Eve;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-timothy.2.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:14",
      "text": "and Adam was not deceived, but the woman was deceived and became a transgressor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-timothy.2.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:15",
      "text": "Yet woman will be saved through bearing children, if she continues in faith and love and holiness, with modesty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
